for (i in 1:10) {

print("TTE.PA.Close")
## [1] "TTE.PA.Close"
print(agostino.test(TTE.PA$TTE.PA.Close,alternative ="two.sided"))
## 
##  D'Agostino skewness test
## 
## data:  TTE.PA$TTE.PA.Close
## skew = 0.23745, z = 6.29248, p-value = 3.124e-10
## alternative hypothesis: data have a skewness
